            section#staff.colorblock: .plx-container 
                h3.title tm
                .plx-card
                    .plx-card-header Test 
                    .plx-card-body Test test test 

            section#minigames.colorblock: .plx-container 
                pre= JSON.stringify(userinfo,null,3)

            //.plx-uncontainer 
            section#quickie.colorblock
                .plx-container(plx-scrollspy="target: h1,h5,p,.slideup,h3; cls: plx-animation-slide-bottom-medium; repeat: true; delay: 120")
                    h5.subhead Newbies Guide
                    h1.title How to Pollux 101
                    div
                        h3.lead
                            | Pollux can be potentially complex depending on your needs. So here's a really compact intro to get started with Pollux:

                    p.lead: i I want Pollux for
                    .plx-grid.plx-grid-large.plx-flex-around.slideup(plx-scrollspy="target: li; cls: plx-animation-slide-left-small; repeat: true; delay: 60")
                        .plx-width-1-1(class="plx-width-1-2@s")
                            h3.subhead Softmod and User Management 
                                p.lead
                            | Moderation is not Pollux's focus, but she provides some features on that.
                            ul.plx-text-muted.plx-list.featli
                                li 
                                    span Use 
                                    code.mistyblue p!modrole 
                                        code [@Role]
                                    span to assign a moderation/administrative role. These users can edit server settings in the <a href=/dashboard>Dashboard</a>
                                li 
                                    span Use 
                                    code.mistyblue p!muterole 
                                        code [@Role]
                                    span to assign a role for muted users. These users cannot type in any channels.
                                li 
                                    span Automatic roles added to users in certain levels can be set up only in the Dashboard. Insert the role, and the level. 0 to add it upon joining.
                                li
                                    span Self-assignable roles can be set in the Dashboard, and via Discord using 
                                    code.mistyblue p!autorole add 
                                        code [@Role Name] 
                                        code ["shorthand"]
                                    span where "shorthand" (quotes required), are something other than the rolename to be used to aquire the role using
                                    code.mistyblue p!roleme shorthand
                                    span , or 
                                    code.mistyblue p!roleme Role Name
                                li 
                                    span Disable commands and features with
                                    code.mistyblue p!disable 
                                        code [command]
                            
                        .plx-width-1-1(class="plx-width-1-2@s")
                            h3.subhead.subhead--light Cosmetics, Lootoxes and Profiles

                            p.lead
                            | Pollux's cosmetics suite is enabled by default.
                            ul.plx-text-muted.plx-list.featli
                                li 
                                    span Use 
                                    code.mistyblue p!disable 
                                        code [DROPS | EXP | LVUP]
                                    span to disable Lootboxes / Experience Points / Level Up Messages
                                li 
                                    span Use 
                                    code.mistyblue p!lootbox
                                    span to see if you hold any boxes. Or
                                    code.mistyblue p!lootbox open 
                                        code [tier (
                                            span.optional C | U | R | SR | UR | EV
                                            | )]
                                    span to open a Lootbox of a specific rarity tier. Then 
                                    code.mistyblue reroll | keep
                                    span depending on whether you like the contents or not. Rerolls cost <b>Rubines</b>, so do it wisely.
                                    
                                li 
                                    span The best, hassle-free way to get your Rubines is with
                                    code.mistyblue p!daily
                                    span , the more you do it, the more Rubines you get every day.
                                    
                                li
                                    span If you want to give a Lootbox to someone else, do
                                    code.mistyblue p!trade box 
                                        code [@User]
                                    span , then the number of the tier displayed in the message afterwards, then "ok".
                                    
                                li
                                    span Equip your cosmetics using the Dashboard
                                    
                                li
                                    span Marriage relies in the <a href="/crafting">Crafting System</a> give it a good read and also try 
                                    code.mistyblue p!marry help
                                    span , or
                                    code.mistyblue p!craft help
                                    span  if you still cannot understand it 
                        hr(style="margin:30px")
                        p.lead Pretty much everything can be set up from the Dashboard, if you find too difficult to understand the commands, try using it instead, it is easier, faster and more natural than typing a bunch of words!
    .sspycon(class="plx-visible@s")
        .plx-nav(plx-scrollspy-nav="closest: li; scroll: true; offset: 80" plx-parallax="opacity:1,1,1,0; target: #content-roll" ).homenav
            li: a(href="#top")
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#start")
                    i.fas.fa-coffee
                    span About
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#features")
                    i.fas.fa-candy-cane
                    span Features
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#economy")
                    i.fas.fa-gem
                    span Economy
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#partners")
                    i.fas.fa-feather-alt
                    span Partners
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#minigames")
                    i.fas.fa-gamepad
                    span Minigames
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#team")
                    i.fas.fa-user-astronaut
                    span Staff
            li
                .homenav-item: a(href="#quickie")
                    i.fas.fa-rocket
                    span Quickstart   


        style footer{margin-top:200px}




block scripts
    //script.
        if ("serviceWorker" in navigator) {
        if (navigator.serviceWorker.controller) {
            console.log("[PWA Builder] active service worker found, no need to register");
        } else {
            // Register the service worker
            navigator.serviceWorker
            .register("pwabuilder-sw.js", {
                scope: "./"
            })
            .then(function (reg) {
                console.log("[PWA Builder] Service worker has been registered for scope: " + reg.scope);
            });
        }
        }
